### Bug fix
- Bug description.
skywalking can't collect data in 20+ seconds .eg :
```
public class JedisTest {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        Jedis j = new Jedis("xx.xx.xx.xx", 6379);
        for (int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
            Thread.sleep(1000L);
            String users = j.get("users");
            System.out.println(users);
        }
        LockSupport.park();
    }
}
```
- reason?

1.DiscoveryRestServiceClient.run() init run in 0 seconds, interval is 60 seconds.
2.GRPCChannelManager.run() init run in 0 seconds, interval is 30 seconds.
3.ServiceManager.bootedServices is HashMap , GRPCChannelManager.run() always before  DiscoveryRestServiceClient.run()

- How to fix?
1.ServiceManager.bootedServices changed to LinckedHashMap , to make sure DiscoveryRestServiceClient.run() before GRPCChannelManager.run() 
2.DiscoveryRestServiceClient.run() sychronized instead of asychronized

:skywalking 3.2.6-2017
